2. Use the Peruvian graph, Test the Louvain and Leiden algorithm¶

In [5]:
library(igraph)

# Define the full file path
file_path <- "https://github.com/2025DACSS-CSSmeths/HW2/raw/refs/heads/main/MyGraphs/Peru.graphml"

# Load the Peru graph
Peru <- read_graph(file_path, format = "graphml")

#making sure to have the name attribute
V(Peru)$name=V(Peru)$id
In [6]:
#Draw the network
set.seed(111) # use this to get same results as me

plot.igraph(Peru)
In [8]:
#The LOUVAIN method
set.seed(321)

Peru_lv <- cluster_louvain(Peru)
sizes(Peru_lv)
#Plot
plot(Peru_lv, Peru,
     layout = layout_with_kk, 
     main="Louvain Solution")

Community sizes

13 11  4  3
In [9]:
modularity(Peru, membership(Peru_lv),directed = FALSE)
0.288614540466392
In [6]:
#The LEIDEN method
Peru_ld <- cluster_leiden(Peru)
sizes(Peru_ld)

In [10]:
# Too many communities, be explicit about the objective functionset 
set.seed(123)
Peru_ld_mod <- cluster_leiden(Peru,
                              objective_function ="modularity")

sizes(Peru_ld_mod)

11 11  6  3
In [28]:
plot(Peru_ld_mod, Peru,
     layout = layout_with_kk, 
     main="Leiden Solution-using modularity")
In [11]:
modularity(Peru, membership(Peru_ld_mod))
#The first one has a slightly better score, #The LOUVAIN method should be choosen

library(igraph)

# Too many communities, be explicit about the objective functionset 
set.seed(123)
Peru_ld_mod <- cluster_leiden(Peru,
                              objective_function ="modularity")

sizes(Peru_ld_mod)
#plot

     layout = layout_with_kk,

Error in cluster_leiden(Seattle): At vendor/cigraph/src/community/leiden.c:1000 : Leiden algorithm is only implemented for undirected graphs. Invalid value
Traceback:

1. cluster_leiden(Seattle)

Both the above LOUVAIN method and LEIDEN method does't work, because these algorithm only work for undirected graphs.

In [16]:
#Girvan-Newman (Edge Betweenness)

set.seed(123)
Seattle_gn <- cluster_edge_betweenness(Seattle,directed = F)

sizes(Seattle_gn)

Community sizes

38  1  1  1  1  1  1  1  1

     layout = layout_with_kk, 
     main="Girvan-Newman Solution")
